<div class="body" id="fhbody-173648240">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-173648240" class="p">
			
		 	
				An anonymous reader shares a report:<i> With Windows 11 24H2 all geared up to have AI-intensive applications, Microsoft has added a code that will warn you if your PC <a href="https://www.tomshardware.com/software/operating-systems/windows-11-will-reportedly-display-a-watermark-if-your-pc-does-not-support-ai-requirements">does not meet the hardware requirements</a>, according to code dug up by Twitter/X sleuth Albacore. The warning will be displayed as a watermark so you know that you cannot use certain AI-powered built-in apps because of an unsupported CPU.</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
